{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Stage-1 BM25F candidate generation over digests + graph-exclusion filter\n\n## Why\nStage 1 must narrow a few hundred tickets to ~20 candidates cheaply and deterministically, with no LLM and no embeddings, and must NOT surface a ticket's own already-related work (parents/children/siblings/linked) — the top source of \"legitimately related but distinct\" false flags.\n\n## What\n- A brute-force BM25F \"More Like This\" scorer (bespoke ~40 LOC: `rank-bm25` provides only UNWEIGHTED BM25, but we need per-field weighting; at n<1000 this is trivial and avoids adding a dependency — consistent with rebar's lean, no-heavy-ML ethos) over the corpus of `ticket_digest` records (from S2). Field-weighted: `problem_keywords` and `component_or_area` high, `propositions`/`key_entities` lower (weights configurable). Query side = the query ticket's freshly-extracted digest (S1), passed in by the caller. Precision knobs (all configurable via the `overlap` typed config): `max_doc_freq` and a stopword list to prune project boilerplate, a `minimum_should_match`-style overlap floor, and `K` (default 20). Returns a typed `OverlapCandidate` list `[{ticket_id, score, matched_terms}]` (this is the interface S7 consumes — stated here so S7 isn't blind to it).\n- Graph-exclusion filter applied BEFORE scoring, dropping the query ticket's parents, children, siblings (same parent), and any ticket already linked by any relation. A NEW helper `src/rebar/llm/overlap/graph.py::related_ticket_ids(ticket_id) -> set[str]` that REUSES the existing public `src/rebar/_engine_support/descendants.py::list_descendants` for descendants, and adds ancestors (walk `parent_id` up), siblings (same `parent_id`), and linked tickets (from reduced `deps`) on top. It does NOT refactor `next_batch.py` (descendants.py already provides the traversal).\n- Corpus tickets whose digest is absent or stale (per S2 freshness) are SKIPPED (never matched on raw text — no fallback). \"Stale\" = S2's content-hash/version mismatch (not an age threshold). Count skipped tickets and log the count so a silently-degraded (cold) run is distinguishable from a healthy one.\n- Error handling: a graph-read or scoring exception is caught, logged, and yields an empty candidate list (the overlap step then surfaces nothing) — never propagates to block review_plan.\n\n## Dependencies\nS1 (`ticket_digest` schema + fields), S2 (digest store + freshness). Digest fields are DEFINED in S1, not pre-existing code.\n\n## Scope\n- New `src/rebar/llm/overlap/retrieve.py` (BM25F + candidate type); new `src/rebar/llm/overlap/graph.py` (`related_ticket_ids`, reusing `descendants.list_descendants`); `overlap` config weights/knobs in `VerifyConfig (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, `[tool.rebar][verify]`, new `overlap_*` fields alongside `require_plan_review_for_claim`/`enable_code_review` — an existing non-reserved gate-config section, env-overridable)`.\n- OUT: the LLM judge (S6), review-plan wiring (S7). Interface contract for S7: `retrieve(query_digest, corpus, exclude) -> list[OverlapCandidate]`.\n\n## Testing\n- Unit `tests/unit/test_overlap_retrieve.py`: top-K ordering; graph-exclusion drops parents/children/siblings/linked (fixture graph); absent/stale digests skipped + skip-count logged; boilerplate fixture (shared boilerplate, distinct work) does NOT rank as a match; knobs configurable; a graph-read error yields [] not an exception. Perf: assert <10ms for a 300-digest corpus.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Given a query digest and corpus, returns top-K (default 20) `OverlapCandidate`s by field-weighted BM25F; <10ms at ~300 digests; verified by `pytest tests/unit/test_overlap_retrieve.py::{test_topk,test_perf}`.\n- [ ] Candidates EXCLUDE the query ticket's parents, children, siblings, and already-linked tickets, via the shared `related_ticket_ids` helper; verified by `::test_graph_exclusion`.\n- [ ] Corpus tickets with absent/stale digests (S2 content-hash/version mismatch) are skipped and the skip-count is logged; verified by `::test_cold_skip`.\n- [ ] Boilerplate terms do not drive matches (`max_doc_freq`/stopwords); verified by `::test_boilerplate`.\n- [ ] Field weights, `max_doc_freq`, overlap floor, and `K` are configurable via the `overlap` typed config; a graph-read/scoring error yields an empty list (never blocks the caller).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783573441689437001,"uuid":"9baa521a-7e4a-4e2c-9bc0-3a8d2388e2cc"}